subject: Re: [junit] JUnit 4.0 release candidate 2 Test.None
msgSnippet: Sadly, not as long as it s defined on an interface--and moving it anywhere else would belie the fact that it s only meaningful to the Test annotaton.  We ll
messageBody:
Sadly, not as long as it's defined on an interface--and moving it
anywhere else would belie the fact that it's only meaningful to the Test
annotaton. We'll probably have to just javadoc it as "hands off".

David Saff

Elliotte Harold wrote:

> David Saff wrote:
>
> > None is the default value of the expected attribute on the Test
> > annotation. It is not intended for outside use. Thanks,
>
> Can this be made non-public then?
